data.description:
(((((( DESCRIPTION ))))))

The space
`
Studio style room (with private kitchen and balcony) in a safe secure gated complex }
_______________________


*** Amenities and connection :

there are excellent public transport connections to the centre and the airport.
5 bus routes + the tram stop are 5 minutes walking away.

- City centre: 5km
great link to the city & its attractions.
20 minutes to the city centre by light rail tram (Luas) redline and 25 Minutes or more (depends on traffic) by bus.

- 17 Min - 30 Min Max (depending on location) by transport to the most popular Streets to visit in Dublin:

- Dame St.
- Temple Bar Area.
- Grafton St.
- St stephen green.
- Mary St and Henry St.
- The Spire/ O'Connell St/O'Connell bridge.
- Trinity College and College Green.
- Guinness Storehouse.
-Phoenix park 12 min by taxi (around €12).


- Dublin Airport :
It's easy to get from/to the airport as the airport bus is just 2 stops by tram from/to the apartment and Vice Versa.

- Big grocery shops (Aldi, Lidl and SuperValu and Centra shop) are 5-10 minutes walk away from the apartment, also Pubs, restaurants takeaways.
________________________

*** The Space :

the space is fully set up to offer a perfect base for someone to set themselves up for a temporary period.

- This studio style room inside an apartment with a private kitchen and balcony in a safe secure gated complex, has a double bed and a large comfortable 4 seater sofa that can fit a third person. along with WiFi, hot power shower available all day long, fresh linen, towels, and complementary toiletries provided ( shampoo, shower gel, hand soap, and toilet tissue).

- private kitchen, there is a fridge, microwave, kettle, glasses, cups, plates, cutlery, small pot and frying pan, hob and oven ( please note there is no possibility to use the dishwasher).

- the bathroom is shared between 2 rooms only. you have your access door to the bathroom from the corridor and the second door (inside the bathroom for the other guests).

- Washing/drying service available €10
________________________

*** Guest access :

The booking will be for the Studio style bedroom with balcony and there are no common spaces other than the entrance to the property and the bathroom.
________________________

*** House rules :

1. Suitable for people between 18 and 50s.

2. Respect the quiet hours from 22:00 to 8:00.

3. No unregistered guests /visitors allowed.

4. Take extra care of your keys/fob. If lost, a €200 fee will apply.

5. Damage or missing item will be reported to Airbnb and billed to guests.
________________________

*** Other Notes :

Check-in starts from 17:30 (5:30pm).
Check-out anytime until 12 pm (noon).

Please notice there is No possibility to check in before 17:30 or check out later than 12 noon. but if required you can store your luggage before the check in time or after the check out time.
data.title: Studio style ROOM/20 min to Centre- Airport 30 min

reviews.comments: We stayed with Ed for 1 month. We could check in on the day that we booked and communication was quick, clear and efficient. Ed provided a very clear description of the location, how to get in, pubs/shops/etc around and answered all our questions very quickly. Ed was very kind in his way of communication. The studio looks like the pictures, however it can use a little ''clean up'' cupboard doors in the kitchen broken, dirty kitchen wall, some hole in the wall, some things getting loose etc. It didnt bother us at all, the place is more than fine, its just little things that maybe one day deserve some attention. Its a good place if you have to work, there is dedicated place for that and its comfortable. What was a bit of a challenge at times was the shared bathroom not everyone understood to open the doors after use, and the slamming doors at times could be annoying. Overall, good experience, thank you so much Ed!

Por el precio el lugar me parece fabuloso. Cocina, sala, cama y un lugar para trabajar. El wifi servía bien, había agua caliente y la calefacción funciona perfectamente.
El cuarto estaba un poco sucio cuando llegamos, la cocina en particular era un desastre y el balcón tenía colillas de cigarro tiradas. Pero dándole una limpieza era un excelente lugar.
La ubicación está alejada del centro, peor muy cerca de la estación de Lúas y de autobuses que te llevan. En 30 minutos o menos estás en el centro.
La atención de Ed y las instalaciones fueron muy claras.

localizedReview.comments:
For the price, the place seems fabulous to me. Kitchen, living room, bed and a place to work. The wifi worked well, there was hot water and the heating works perfectly.
The room was a little dirty when we arrived, the kitchen in particular was a mess and the balcony had cigarette butts lying around. But if you cleaned it, it was a great place.
The location is far from downtown, but very close to the Lúas station and buses that take you there. In 30 minutes or less you're downtown.
Ed's service and the facilities were very clear.

reviews.comments: Comfortable accommodation in a quiet area, well connected with transport (both luas and bus). Bathroom always clean and immediate responses from the host for any need.

A very complicated entry process.
Large door to balcony has broken hinge at the top, making the door unsafe to open. I told Ed about this as soon as i noticed it. He didn’t believe me.
Drawer front off bottom drawer in kitchen.
No washer or dryer in unit as stated in Airbnb ad.
No tea towel or plug for kitchen sink, even though washing up detergent provided.
Lights over bed had no globes.
Toilet constantly flushes.
Wall next to microwave was filthy.
Travel to city much more than 20 minutes as stated in ad.
Numerous wall repairs incomplete and messy.

Alojamiento tal cual de describe en el anuncio. Ed nos dejó hacer check in antes y respondía rápido. El recinto es amplio y en una zona familiar y linda a 5 minutos del tranvía y de fácil acceso al centro. Los acabados del cuarto podrían estar en mejores condiciones al igual que la iluminación.  El balcón le dio un toque especial.

localizedReview.comments: Accommodation as described in the listing. Ed let us check in earlier and he was quick to respond. The enclosure is spacious and in a family and beautiful area 5 minutes from the tram and easily access to the center. The finishes in the room could be in better condition as well as the lighting.  The balcony gave it a special touch.

reviews.comments: Logement à proximité du centre de Dublin, facilement accessible, sécurisé, au calme et suffisamment grand pour 3 adultes. Hôte très réactif et arrangeant.

localizedReview.comments: Home close to Dublin center, easily accessible, secure, quiet and large enough for 3 adults. Very responsive and accommodating host.

reviews.comments: It was really nice. Everything went smoothly!

My mum and I had a lovely stay.  Ed was comfortable and the apartment was nice and clean. Ed recommended local pubs/ restaurants which were lovely, and it’s a short tram ride into town. Ed was super responsive, friendly and helpful before/ during and after our stay. Thank you for having us :)

10 de 10, totalmente recomendable, Ed fue muy amable en todo momento y respondía cualquier pregunta y duda de forma muy rápida, aparte de que se nos retrasó el vuelo y nos dejó quedarnos un par de horas más lo que fue un detalle increíble, si me coincide de volver a visitar esta ciudad no dudaré en alojarme contigo.

localizedReview.comments: 10 of 10, totally recommended, Ed was very kind at all times and answered any questions and doubts very quickly, apart from the fact that the flight was delayed and allowed us to stay a couple of hours longer than it was an incredible detail, if it coincides with me to visit this city again I will not hesitate to stay with you.

reviews.comments: My girlfriend and I loved the apartment, everything is very organized and beautiful!
Great stay, would come back again
Ed is a flexible and reactive host. he is also very helpful with clear instruction to get the room from the airport or the city center.

Ed bravissima persona sempre a disposizione, una  persona genuina che purtroppo non ho avuto l’opportunità di conoscerlo da vivo ma spero un giorno d’incontralo! Grazie ancora ed spero alla prossima volta! :)

localizedReview.comments: And very good person always available, a genuine person who unfortunately I did not have the opportunity to meet him alive but I hope one day to meet him! Thanks again and I hope to see you next time! :)

reviews.comments: Im großen und ganzen war der Aufenthalt okay. Die Kommunikation mit Ed war spitze, er war immer erreichbar. Aber die Wohnung selbst, der Flur und das Bad waren nicht sehr angenehm. Man konnte die Öffentlichen Verkehrsmittel gut erreichen. Ausstattung der Küche sehr arm. Für ein paar Tage Dublin ist es okay. Die Wohnung ist in einem Familienviertel.

localizedReview.comments: Overall, the stay was okay. The communication with Ed was great, he was always available. But the apartment itself, the hallway and bathroom were not very pleasant. You could easily reach public transport. Kitchen equipment very poor. For a few days Dublin it's okay. The apartment is located in a family neighborhood.

reviews.comments: Notre séjour chez Ed à juste été parfait. Personne très réactive, accueil et explications de la prise des clefs super il peut pas y avoir plus précis. Ed est très agréable, à l’écoute et j’en passe. Logement conforme à la description, je recommande les yeux fermés.

localizedReview.comments: Our stay at Ed's was just perfect. Very responsive person, welcome and explanations of the taking of the keys great there may not be more specific. Ed is very nice, attentive and so on. Listing as described, I would recommend it without a second thought.

reviews.comments:
Bon rapport qualité prix au vue des tarifs à Dublin, logement proche du tram ( environ 5 min à pied ), 25min du centre.
Logement spacieux, équipé convenablement. Ed a été tres attentif à nos besoins, toujours réactif et amical.

localizedReview.comments:
Good value for money in Dublin rates, accommodation close to the tram ( about 5 min walk ), 25 min to the center.
Spacious accommodation, suitably equipped. Ed was very attentive to our needs, always responsive and friendly.

reviews.comments: I really love to stay and it's a very lovely place I will love to stay again

Ed war ein toller Gastgeber, der stets schnell geantwortet hat, freundlich war und gute Tipps gegeben hat.
Das Badezimmer war sehr sauber und hatte alles was man sich wünscht.
Die Unterkunft lag in einer ruhigen und grünen Gegend, die man super mit den Öffentlichen erreichen konnte.
Die Küche war gut nur leider etwas spärlich ausgestattet.
Alles in einem hatten wir einen schönen Aufenthalt in der Wohnung.

localizedReview.comments:
Ed was a great host who always responded quickly, was friendly and gave good tips.
The bathroom was very clean and had everything you want.
The place was in a quiet and green area that was easy to reach by public transport.
The kitchen was well but unfortunately somewhat sparsely equipped.
All in one we had a lovely stay at the apartment.

reviews.comments: Nous avons passé un super séjour à Dublin et cet Airbnb a grandement contribué à notre expérience mémorable ! Idéalement situé, il était proche du tram et du bus, ce qui nous a permis de nous rendre rapidement et facilement dans le centre-ville. De plus, le fait que l'endroit soit situé dans un clos nous a offert une tranquillité et une sécurité appréciables, nous permettant de nous sentir parfaitement à l'aise. Notre hôte a été incroyablement réactif et toujours présent pour répondre à nos questions et nous aider, ce qui a ajouté une touche supplémentaire à notre séjour. Nous recommandons vivement cet Airbnb à tous ceux qui envisagent de visiter Dublin !

localizedReview.comments: We had a great time in Dublin and this Airbnb made a great contribution to our memorable experience! Conveniently located, it was close to the tram and bus, which allowed us to get to the city center quickly and easily. In addition, the fact that the place is located in an enclosure gave us appreciable tranquility and safety, allowing us to feel perfectly comfortable. Our host was incredibly responsive and always there to answer our questions and help us, which added an extra touch to our stay. We highly recommend this Airbnb to anyone considering visiting Dublin!

reviews.comments:
Ubicación fantástica y conexión excelente hacia el centro de Dublín! Barrio tranquilo y seguro.
Tiendas, farmacias y restaurantes a menos de 10 minutos caminando. Habitación con cocina y balcón precioso! Baño compartido con dos habitaciones más.
Comunicación con Ed excelente! Instrucciones y cuidados muy buenos! Es un súper anfitrión!
Muchas gracias por todo!

localizedReview.comments:
Fantastic location and excellent connection to the center of Dublin! A safe and quiet neighborhood.
Shops, pharmacies and restaurants less than a 10-minute walk away. Room with a lovely kitchen and balcony! Shared bathroom with two more rooms.
Communication with Ed excellent! Very good instructions and care! He's a super host!
Thank you very much for everything!

reviews.comments: It was great both to me and my friends. Good host to whom we didn’t have any issues communication wise. Ed was always available and prompt to help with any pending matter. Would recommend him to other fellow guests and would also be happy to be hosted by him once again. Cheers!

Ed was an amazing host. Communicating with him was excellent and he was quick to reply every time. He was making sure we had a great and comfortable stay. We are new in Ireland and he tried his best to make our new start even easier. We really appreciate him and we believe he is the best host by far.
Was a wonderful stay feeling like home
Second-time stay and it was absolutely a good stay
Nice, modern apartment in a good location and a very helpful host. The check in could be a little bit easier, but once we got in  everything went well.

Prima verblijf dat goed bereikbaar is met het openbaar vervoer in Dublin. Ook is Ed responsief. Enige opmerking is dat het verblijf enig onderhoud aan de muren- en schoonmaak in de keuken nodig heeft.

localizedReview.comments: Excellent stay that is easily accessible by public transportation in Dublin. Ed is also responsive. Only note is that the stay needs some maintenance on the walls and cleaning in the kitchen.

reviews.comments: Ed was proactive and responsive during our stay. Nice and warm accommodation in a serene location with easy access to the Tram to City Centre. I definitely recommend!
Ed was incredibly helpful, the place was well equipped and really cozy

Although the check in process was a bit convoluted, Ed keeps great communication with his guests and helps you with any queries you have.
Overall enjoyed my stay, good value for money, apartment is nice also.
Plenty of amenities around and luas in close proximity aswell. Great for couples aswell. Would recommend.

Appartement calme et reposant, ce logement était parfait pour notre voyage.
Je recommande. Bonne continuation Ed !
The French Guys Jules et Allan

localizedReview.comments:
Quiet and relaxing apartment, this home was perfect for our trip.
I recommend it. Happy hosting Ed!
The French Guys Jules et Allan

reviews.comments: 합리적인 가격, 깔끔하고 난방이 잘 되는 숙소, 친절한 호스트 덕분에 좋은 여행이 되었습니다.

localizedReview.comments: Reasonably priced, tidy and well heated accommodation, and friendly host made a good trip.

reviews.comments:
We had a great time and a peaceful area. ED was the best a
Hoster, responding on time.

Ed was a very good host. He provided detailed instructions to allow smooth check in and over all comfort. We arrived late at night and our check in was smooth and room was warm. The room is really spacious and the kitchen inside the bedroom was an added bonus for light meal preparation. The toilet was very clean and there is a small balcony to sit and watch the sun set. Ed also message the day before check out to find out if everything was fine and if we need any assistance. I cannot find any fault with the service. It was value for money and not far from the city centre.
Ed was a fantastic host! Really quick response time and always answered questions or queries that we had. 100% would stay again.
Very helpful and responsive, gave a lot of help and suggestions with close restraunts and shops etc, good location with short taxi into the centre. Enjoyed our stay very much!

I recommend Ed's studio. It's spacious and warm, with a very comfortable bed and kitchen, a sofa, armchairs, a computer desk, big fridge. It's close to a tram station and the tram comes every 10 minutes and quickly takes you to Dublin. The area is nice and green. Ed is very reactive and helpful, replying very quickly on airbnb.
Great thanks Ed!!!
Quiet and safe neighbourhood. Ed responded to our queries on time. Although there are no common areas, the room itself has what we need.
Ed was super reactive and seemed to really care about my well-being during my stay. The room was nice and clean. The view is cute. I would totally recommend Ed's place.
